<item>
            <title>[LU-10989] lustre_rsync may clear an unconsumed record after a CL_RENAME</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10989</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;lr_replicate()&lt;/tt&gt;, if we see a non-extended rename record then we consume the following record to get the rename source. &lt;tt&gt;lr_clear_cl()&lt;/tt&gt; accounts for this by adding 1 to the endrc if the current record is a rename. However, &lt;tt&gt;lr_clear_cl()&lt;/tt&gt; always does this even if the current record was an extended rename.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="52080">LU-10989</key>
